<!-- Metal Roofing -->

	<div class="page-header"></div>
	<div class="row">
		<div class="col-md-6">
			<h2><strong>Metal Roofing</strong></h2>

			<p class="lead"> When it comes to weighing in on the benefits of a metal roof over a traditional asphalt shingle roof, a metal roof installed by Bryce Roofing's expert installers is an obvious choice for many home owners.</p>

			<p>Most metal roofs come with a 50 year warranty providing decades of protection from the elements. Also, our metal roof systems come with Bryce Roofing's Ten Year <em>No Worries</em> workmanship warranty for your peace of mind</p>

			<p>Metal roofing is on the leading edge of technology with a wide variety of finishes, designs and colors that provide greater energy savings <a href="http://www.energystar.gov/certified-products/detail/roof_products?fuseaction=find_a_product.showProductGroup&pgw_code=RO" target="_blank">compared to most other non-metal roofing products</a> on the market today.</p>

			<p>Beyond the beauty and the protection that a metal roof provides, advantages include:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Good for the environment - 100% recyclable.</li>
				<li>Lower cost over the life of the roof.</li>
				<li>Lower maintenance costs.</li>
				<li>Adds resale value.</li>
				<li>Cool metal roofing has been shown to save up to 40% on <a href="http://rsc.ornl.gov/" target="_blank">energy costs</a>.</li>
				<li>Due to its light weight per unit area, structural savings can be realized in a building when compared to using heavier non-metal roofing alternatives. For re-roofing projects, metal roofing can often be applied over the original roof, saving removal and disposal costs.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</div>

